@qwersd: In my comment (answer) there to lilars I and as in long version of Description which is posted every single day, I have recommended installing Core AVC and DivX. Both have fastest DirectShow filters for a/v.

What player would be used then - is matter of personal preferences. I've said too that I use fastest - Windows Media Player and that Media Player Classic is maybe equally good for some people. And - DivX come equipped with own player (which will use mentioned DivX filters).

However, I am surprised, that people use shit as ddshow or K-Lite or CCCP packed crap - and majority already have installed perfect Matroska player (if one installs AC3 filter) or MP4 player which is 6.8 TIMES faster - DivX player, pure gold, and WMP is a part of OS already.
